  "body": "### Description\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\nThe name entered during account creation is not shown to other contacts even if both users are added in each-others contacts\r\n**Please note,** new name is shown immediately, If the name is changed on Profile screen\r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\n`User B` sees the name which was entered by `User A` during account creation\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\n`User B` sees default (e.g. Splendid Useless Racerunner) name of  `User A` instead of entered name\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n[comment]: # (Describe how we can replicate the bug step by step.)\r\n\r\n- Open Status on 2 devices\r\n- Enter and Confirm password on 2 devices\r\n- Enter unique names on 2 devices after account creation\r\n- As `User A` open `Profile` screen and click `SHARE MY CONTACT CODE`\r\n- As `User B`: click on `+` button than on `Start New Chat` and than on `QR code icon` in order to scan the QR code, as result one-to-one chat with `User A` is opened.\r\n- As `User A` open the chat with `User B` on Home screen and click `Add to contacts`\r\n\r\n\r\n* Status version: `77e6f455`\r\n* Operating System: Android and iOS",
